  34:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c **** /**
  35:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****   @ingroup groupInterpolation
  36:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****  */
  37:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c **** 
  38:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c **** /**
  39:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * @defgroup LinearInterpolate Linear Interpolation
  40:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  41:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * Linear interpolation is a method of curve fitting using linear polynomials.
  42:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * Linear interpolation works by effectively drawing a straight line between two neighboring samp
  43:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  44:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \par
  45:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \image html LinearInterp.gif "Linear interpolation"
  46:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  47:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \par
  48:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * A  Linear Interpolate function calculates an output value(y), for the input(x)
  49:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * using linear interpolation of the input values x0, x1( nearest input values) and the output va
  50:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  51:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \par Algorithm:
  52:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * <pre>
  53:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *       y = y0 + (x - x0) * ((y1 - y0)/(x1-x0))
  54:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *       where x0, x1 are nearest values of input x
  55:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *             y0, y1 are nearest values to output y
  56:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * </pre>
  57:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  58:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \par
  59:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * This set of functions implements Linear interpolation process
  60:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * for Q7, Q15, Q31, and floating-point data types.  The functions operate on a single
  61:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * sample of data and each call to the function returns a single processed value.
  62:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * <code>S</code> points to an instance of the Linear Interpolate function data structure.
  63:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * <code>x</code> is the input sample value. The functions returns the output value.
  64:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    *
  65:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * \par
  66:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * if x is outside of the table boundary, Linear interpolation returns first value of the table
  67:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    * if x is below input range and returns last value of table if x is above range.
  68:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c ****    */
  69:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/InterpolationFunctions/arm_linear_interp_f32.c **** 
